latestPosts.caption:
A year ago, a reel popped up on my feed with a line that hit me deeply: “We could never be in our twenties again, dancing with strangers in a random street in a new country.” I remember watching it and feeling this quiet longing in my heart, almost like I was manifesting it for myself in that moment. Little did I know, that wish would come true in the most unexpected way, just a week ago, in Nice, France.

It was one of those spontaneous evenings. Me and kalyan had been enjoying some wine, wandering through the charming streets of Nice. We weren’t expecting anything special but then, on a random street, something magical happened. A group had gathered around musicians playing traditional French instruments. The music was lively, drawing everyone in. We stood there, captivated by the moment, wondering what was going on.

Out of nowhere, a pretty young woman approached us. Without speaking a word of English, she smiled and gestured for us to join her in the dance. At first, I hesitated. I’m not exactly a dancer, and the idea of jumping in with strangers made me nervous. But there was something about the moment that felt too good to let slip away. So, with a deep breath, I joined in.

The dancers, with their warmth and patience, began teaching us the steps—simple, joyful moves that flowed to the rhythm of the French music and the enchanting circle dance(Cercle circassien). I felt like I was being swept into a dream. The beauty wasn’t just in the dance, but in the connection we shared, despite language barriers, despite the fact that we were all strangers. There was a collective joy, a sense of freedom in that simple, unspoken moment. 

I have no pictures, no videos. But that’s what made it even more special—because I was *there*, completely present in that fleeting moment. It was a dream come true, not just because of the dance, but because of the feeling that I had somehow, quietly, manifested this exact moment a year ago. I’m so grateful that I did. 💕

latestPosts.caption:
2024 has truly been an incredible year in my life, filled with growth, adventure, and unforgettable memories.🧚🏻‍♀️ I’ve had the opportunity to travel extensively, exploring new places and immersing myself in different cultures. 🌸One of the highlights was being able to show my parents around the US, sharing special moments with them in some of the country’s most beautiful spots. Along the way, I’ve collected countless fun experiences and moments that will stay with me forever. 
On a personal level, I’ve also made significant strides toward my forever body weight dream, 🏋️‍♀️ achieving a level of fitness I’ve never experienced before. Though I haven’t quite hit the final goal yet, I’ve never been fitter in my life. Looking back, 2023 and 2024 stand out as the best years of my life, filled with a sense of accomplishment and joy that I’ll carry into the future.

How was your 2024? Let me know. 🫶🏻
